{% set basicColgroupCode %}<table>
  <caption>Team Schedule</caption>
  <colgroup>
    <col />
    <col style="background: oklch(from var(--color-interactive) l c h / 0.05);" />
    <col />
    <col style="background: oklch(from var(--color-interactive) l c h / 0.05);" />
  </colgroup>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Name</th>
      <th scope="col">Monday</th>
      <th scope="col">Tuesday</th>
      <th scope="col">Wednesday</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>Alice</td><td>9am-5pm</td><td>Remote</td><td>9am-5pm</td>
    </tr>
    <!-- More rows... -->
  </tbody>
</table>{% endset %}

{% set spanAttributeCode %}<table>
  <colgroup span="1"></colgroup>
  <colgroup span="3" style="background: oklch(95% 0.02 200);">
  </colgroup>
  <!-- Spans 3 columns with a tinted background -->
</table>{% endset %}

{% set colWidthsCode %}<table>
  <colgroup>
    <col style="width: 30%;" />
    <col style="width: 25%;" />
    <col style="width: 25%;" />
    <col style="width: 20%;" />
  </colgroup>
  <!-- Column widths are proportional -->
</table>{% endset %}

{% set cssLimitationsCode %}/* Only these properties work on col/colgroup: */
/* background, width, border (with collapse), visibility: collapse */

/* For text-align, padding, color, font — target cells instead: */
td:nth-child(2),
th:nth-child(2) {
  text-align: end;
}

/* Or use VB's data-numeric attribute: */
/* <th data-numeric>Amount</th> */{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;colgroup&gt;</code> element groups one or more columns in a <a href="/docs/elements/native/table/"><code>&lt;table&gt;</code></a> for structural or styling purposes. It must appear after the <a href="/docs/elements/native/caption/"><code>&lt;caption&gt;</code></a> (if present) and before any <a href="/docs/elements/native/thead/"><code>&lt;thead&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/tbody/"><code>&lt;tbody&gt;</code></a>, or <a href="/docs/elements/native/tfoot/"><code>&lt;tfoot&gt;</code></a> elements.</p>
    <p>A <code>&lt;colgroup&gt;</code> can either use the <code>span</code> attribute to cover multiple columns as a single group, or contain individual <a href="/docs/elements/native/col/"><code>&lt;col&gt;</code></a> elements for per-column control. These two modes are mutually exclusive: if <code>&lt;col&gt;</code> children are present, the <code>span</code> attribute is ignored.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>When to Use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Column widths:</strong> set fixed or proportional widths for specific columns</li>
      <li><strong>Column highlighting:</strong> apply background colors to draw attention to specific columns</li>
      <li><strong>Semantic grouping:</strong> group related columns together (e.g., "H1 columns" vs "H2 columns" in a multi-header table)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>When Not Needed</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Simple tables:</strong> where all columns have equal treatment and auto-sized widths</li>
      <li><strong>Cell-level styling:</strong> when styles need to vary within a column, target cells directly with CSS</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <p>This demo shows a table with alternating column backgrounds applied via <code>&lt;col&gt;</code> elements inside a <code>&lt;colgroup&gt;</code>.</p>

    <browser-window src="/docs/snippets/demos/table-colgroup.html" url="table-colgroup.html" title="Table with colgroup column highlighting" shadow></browser-window>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Colgroup with col elements">{{ basicColgroupCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Using <code>span</code></h3>
    <p>The <code>span</code> attribute applies properties to multiple consecutive columns without individual <code>&lt;col&gt;</code> elements.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Colgroup with span attribute">{{ spanAttributeCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <h3>Column Widths</h3>
    <p>Set proportional or fixed widths on <code>&lt;col&gt;</code> elements for consistent column sizing.</p>
    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Setting column widths">{{ colWidthsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>CSS Limitations</h2>
    <p>The CSS specification only allows a limited set of properties on <code>&lt;colgroup&gt;</code> and <a href="/docs/elements/native/col/"><code>&lt;col&gt;</code></a> elements.</p>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Property</th>
          <th scope="col">Supported</th>
          <th scope="col">Notes</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>background</code></td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>Background color and images</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>width</code></td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>Column width (fixed or percentage)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>border</code></td>
          <td>Partial</td>
          <td>Only with <code>border-collapse: collapse</code> (VB default)</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>visibility</code></td>
          <td>Yes</td>
          <td>Only the <code>collapse</code> value</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>padding</code></td>
          <td>No</td>
          <td>Apply to <a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th&gt;</code></a>/<a href="/docs/elements/native/td/"><code>&lt;td&gt;</code></a> instead</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>text-align</code></td>
          <td>No</td>
          <td>Use <code>data-numeric</code> or target cells with CSS</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p>For properties not supported on column groups, target cells with CSS selectors or use VB's <code>data-numeric</code> attribute for right-aligned columns.</p>
    <code-block language="css" show-lines label="Targeting cells when col properties are limited">{{ cssLimitationsCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Attribute</th>
          <th scope="col">Value</th>
          <th scope="col">Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>span</code></td>
          <td>Positive integer</td>
          <td>Number of columns the group spans. Cannot be used when <code>&lt;col&gt;</code> children are present.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Visual distinction:</strong> column background colors help users track data across rows, but ensure sufficient contrast</li>
      <li><strong>Not a replacement for headers:</strong> <code>&lt;colgroup&gt;</code> does not replace proper <a href="/docs/elements/native/th/"><code>&lt;th&gt;</code></a> headers with <code>scope</code> attributes</li>
      <li><strong>Column relationships:</strong> helps assistive technologies understand column groupings in complex tables</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Related Elements</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/elements/native/col/"><code>&lt;col&gt;</code></a> - individual column within a colgroup</li>
